I have long believed that Hutton has a scholastic bias and even an English bias on Pagan traditions. He does eceleent research nut seems a bit myopic for my tastes. It&#039;s good to see some people taking a better look at the folklore and the documented older traditions. It wasn&#039;t all born in the mind of Gerald Gardner.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>BDT!</p>
<p>I have long believed that Hutton has a scholastic bias and even an English bias on Pagan traditions. He does eceleent research nut seems a bit myopic for my tastes. It&#8217;s good to see some people taking a better look at the folklore and the documented older traditions. It wasn&#8217;t all born in the mind of Gerald Gardner.</p>
