I just can&#039;t get over the kind of idiocy that passes for &quot;rigor&quot; these days.    It&#039;s like...all the Pagans are fighting each other to prove that they are not &quot;fluffy bunnies&quot;  (i.e. effeminate).   And so they rush to defend arguments that seem &quot;objective&quot; simply because they do not challenge conventional histories very much.   It&#039;s a way of boosting their own credibility by disparaging a more marginalized view.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Thank you Max!   I wish we had more people writing so intelligently about this subject.   </p>
<p>I just can&#8217;t get over the kind of idiocy that passes for &#8220;rigor&#8221; these days.    It&#8217;s like&#8230;all the Pagans are fighting each other to prove that they are not &#8220;fluffy bunnies&#8221;  (i.e. effeminate).   And so they rush to defend arguments that seem &#8220;objective&#8221; simply because they do not challenge conventional histories very much.   It&#8217;s a way of boosting their own credibility by disparaging a more marginalized view.</p>
